<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98800619516191></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98800619516191><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=5688&mid=98800619516191>RE: Level to Make</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=5688&mid=98800619516191#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=27649><span id=Guru>Palarran</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>117 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Apr 23rd 2:09 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.78]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Actually there is no simple answer to the "level to make?" question here.  It depends what your goal is...<br><br>From reports I've read from more skilled tailors, my impression is:<br>If you want a 50-75% success rate, your skill will have to approach 250.  If 25% is good enough, then getting your skill to 200 should do.  5%?  Anytime from 131 on would be appropriate.  (Don't want to waste a potential skill increase while you still have much easier ways to skill up...)<br><br>Cobalt drake appears to be more difficult than the rest of the velious leathers, so I would expect the minimum 5% success rate for a while, probably not starting to increase until somewhere in the 150-180 range.<br><br>For certain items even the 5% success rate may be acceptable.  Once I get some of those darn drake eggs I'll certainly be attempting the belt, which would be far more useful to me than this bracer.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
